            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> if the computer is suspended the timer is paused\r\n\r\nThis is what I would expect for `:uptime`. If the computer running Nvim is suspended, then Nvim is not \"up\".\r\n\r\nHow long Nvim has been actually running is more useful to me than the literal real time since I started Nvim.\r\n\r\nI admit that what the behavior \"should\" be is a bit subjective. As long as it's documented, both ways are fine.",
