        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I agree that it's a bit subjective, and a whole ton of stackexchange questions show that a lot of people think that's also how `uptime(1)` should behave. :smile: \r\n\r\nStill, I think with `:uptime` having the same name and intended function as the shell command, matching the behavior of `uptime(1)` is better.",
