        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> think that's also how `uptime(1)` should behave\r\n\r\nThat included me! Until just now I thought that was how `uptime(1)` worked, until I checked for myself and learned I was wrong.\r\n\r\n> Still, I think with `:uptime` having the same name and intended function as the shell command, matching the behavior of `uptime(1)` is better.\r\n\r\nYeah, so the choice is either matching `uptime(1)` or being intuitive. I suppose since \"intuitive\" is subjective and \"matching `uptime(1)`\" is very standardized, we should probably merge this PR. Sucks tho, since I prefer the other way...",
